{'id': 12425056, 'body': "Hey, so first off now sure why you're having issues emailing, but if for some reason the SDK I use to report bugs in-app isn't working (More -> Help & Support), you can always send an email to hello@getslopes.com.

There is a complication for Slopes! Depending on where you put it it'll show the current recording status, and in some positions it'll show you the vertical recorded so far today.

Drop me an email with what bugs you're seeing!", 'modified': '2019-12-16T15:37:31Z'}

{'id': 7876119, 'body': "Slopes totally has a map with everything! Hit the lifts & runs button that's there and you'll see a breakdown of stats run by run, on maps and even in 3d.

In addition, there is also a way to fix the car issue. Hit the edit button when checking out your day (button is in the top right) and you can use the Lift & Run editor to remove the time you left Slopes recording in the car.

Hope that helps clear everything up!", 'modified': '2019-03-24T15:53:57Z'}

{'id': 12124945, 'body': 'The core of Slopes hasn't changed, it's just gotten cleaned up a bit. Record your day on the record tab, save it, and then check out your day's stats in the logbook (used to be the "history" tab). That still has the same daily summary screen and then the detailed timeline screen.

There's some great quick-start guides at blog.getslopes.com that just got rolled out that might help shed some light on various aspects of Slopes.

If you have anything specific you're having issues with, you can use the Help & Support under the More tab to get in touch.', 'modified': '2019-11-29T15:07:14Z'}

{'id': 11001136, 'body': 'It is totally early, I said so in the release notes ;). Launching an iPad app with all the new iOS 13 multi window stuff, and supporting as many iOS 13 features as I did on day 1, was more important to me than keeping around 12 support. It‚Äôs hard to balance it all as a solo developer, but doing that while not breaking things in iOS 12 would have been a lot of extra work. I‚Äôd rather spend that time on the *other* amazing new features coming out in a few months. ;)

Part of my decision was that everyone who already has Slopes will keep their working copy and it will keep working on 12. Plus by the time the season starts in 2 months in the northern hemisphere the vast majority of Slopes users will be upgraded to 13. In always 85%+ by then, even when I keep support for old versions around. 

It‚Äôs always a tricky balance, but this is what I needed to do. Hope you understand!', 'modified': '2019-10-01T14:43:50Z'}
